19:T8ef,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does it take to implement AI in a business in Qatar?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For an SME, the planning phase takes 30 days using the AI Navigator framework. The first implementation phase — deploying your highest-priority AI use case — typically takes a further 4–8 weeks depending on complexity. The full journey from first session to live AI running in your business is usually 2–3 months for Tier 1 use cases."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need a technical team to implement AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Not for the planning phase. The AI Navigator framework is designed for business owners and managers — not developers. You will need technical support for the implementation phase, but the planning process is structured so that any competent developer or technology partner can execute from the written plan you produce."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What industries does the AI Navigator framework work for?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Any business with repeatable workflows. The framework has been applied to retail, logistics, financial services, legal, healthcare, hospitality, real estate, and professional services. The process is industry-agnostic because it starts with your specific workflows rather than assuming what AI should do."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is my data safe if I use AI in Qatar?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Qatar's PDPPL requires that businesses handling customer personal data keep it within Qatar. All AI implementations guided by the AI Navigator framework are designed to be PDPPL-compliant, using infrastructure such as Microsoft Azure Qatar and Ooredoo's Sovereign AI Cloud."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I choose an AI consultant in Qatar?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The most important question to ask any AI consultant is: do you start with the business goal or the tool? A consultant who leads with tool recommendations before understanding your workflows is selling you the wrong thing. The right consultant starts with your business problem, maps your processes, and only recommends tools after the strategy is defined."}}]}f:[["$","$L2",null,{"id":"faq-schema","type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$19"}}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"article-wrap","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/resources/","children":"Resources"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","span",null,{"children":"How to Implement AI in Your Business in Qatar"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"How to Implement AI in Your Business in Qatar"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"Most businesses in Qatar approach AI the wrong way. They start with tools. Someone reads about ChatGPT and signs up. A manager attends a vendor demo and buys a subscription. A team runs a few experiments. Six months later, there are scattered logins, no clear results, and leadership asking what the return on investment actually was."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"This is not a technology problem. It is a planning problem. And it is the most common pattern in AI adoption among businesses in Qatar and across the GCC."}],"$L1a"],"$L1b",["$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22"],"$L23","$L24","$undefined","$L25","$L26"]}]]
